records.addlTxt: See CCAP financial payment plan application for specific monthly due dates for this AFTES
Appointing Counsel at County Assessment, signed and filed.  rmm

Defendant Dominic D Sutton appeared by video.  
Prosecuting attorney Olivia Simmons appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm. 
Indigency hearing proceeded.  Court makes a finding that defendant is indigent.  Court appoints Eric Hailstock as counsel for defendant at the rate of $100.00 per hour.  Attorney Hailstock accepts appointment.  Defendant shall reimburse Milwaukee County at the rate of $100.00 on the 1st of every month, commencing 12/01/22 until paid in full. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means. Case is adjourned to Br. 1.  This hearing will be heard via Zoom.
Status conference scheduled for November 18, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON 09/30/2022. IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR, A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST. 
Court advised Defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Dominic D Sutton in court.  Prosecuting attorney Arthur Kenneth Thexton in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 1. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 1.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 20, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 9/28/22 @ 1:30p
